\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. O. speculum} Link in Schrader,{\i  Jour. für die Bot.}{\b  1799}({\b 2}): 324 (1800). Basal leaves oblong, subobtuse, the cauline lanceolate, acute. Outer perianth-segments 6-8 mm, oblong-ovate, green or yellowish, often brown-striate, glabrous, the lateral patent, the median erect, cucullate; inner 1/4-1/3 as long as the outer, ovate to lanceolate, dark purple, rarely greenish, densely hairy. Labellum up to 13 × 15 mm, dark purple, villous with coloured hairs at margin, deeply 3-lobed, not globose-inflated; lateral lobes patent, obtuse, yellowish in the centre and with darker lines; middle lobe often slightly emarginate, with revolute margin, rarely convex; speculum large, shiny, blue, yellow at margin, sometimes 3-lobed. Connective obtuse. 2n = 36.{\i  Mediterranean region, C. & S. Portugal.} Bl Co ?Cr Ga Gr Hs It Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par

